```java
Java.lang.ClassCastException:
    nl.dionsegijn.konfetti.xml.KonfettiView cannot be cast to android.view.ViewGroup
```

This means that you tried to convert `KonfettiView` into a `ViewGroup` on this line:

```java
dialog.setContentView(R.layout.custom_dialog_achievement);
```

`KonfettiView` DOESN&#39;T implement/extend a layout that does the same with the `ViewGroup` class.

This also means that your XML is wrong; it&#39;s not a layout, it&#39;s a plain ordinary view.

Which means it should look like this instead:

```xml
&lt;nl.dionsegijn.konfetti.KonfettiView
    android:id=&quot;@+id/viewKonfetti&quot;
    android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
    android:layout_height=&quot;match_parent&quot;
    android:layout_gravity=&quot;center&quot;
    android:background=&quot;@color/white&quot;/&gt;
```

---

# But DO NOT Worry! There&#39;s A Workaround:

---

Simply make `nl.dionsegijn.konfetti.xml.KonfettiView` extend a layout.

In your case, make it extend a `LinearLayout` like so:

```java
//...
import android.widget.LinearLayout;
//...
public class KonfettiView extends LinearLayout{
//...
}
//...
```

